@startuml fig-routing-triangle-paths
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Alternative Routing Paths: h1 → h3 through the Triangle

participant "h1\n10.0.1.2" as H1 #FFE0B2
participant "r1" as R1 #E3F2FD
participant "r2" as R2 #BBDEFB
participant "r3" as R3 #BBDEFB
participant "h3\n10.0.3.2" as H3 #FFE0B2

== PATH A — Direct: r1 → r3 (default) ==

H1 -[#43A047]> R1 : ping 10.0.3.2
R1 -[#43A047]> R3 : via 10.0.13.2\n(r1-eth2 → r3-eth2)
R3 -[#43A047]> H3 : delivered

== PATH B — Indirect: r1 → r2 → r3 ==

H1 -[#1565C0]> R1 : ping 10.0.3.2
R1 -[#1565C0]> R2 : via 10.0.12.2\n(r1-eth1 → r2-eth0)
R2 -[#1565C0]> R3 : via 10.0.23.2\n(r2-eth1 → r3-eth1)
R3 -[#1565C0]> H3 : delivered

legend right
  Path A: 2 hops (direct r1 → r3)
  Path B: 3 hops (r1 → r2 → r3)
  Switching paths requires deleting
  the old route on r1 and adding a
  new next-hop. traceroute reveals
  which path is currently in use.
endlegend
@enduml
